item.dc:creator: @AssualtX AssualtX
item.description:
@AssualtX wrote:

[quote=“JKOK, post:4, topic:391762”]acually you dont need jarmaker because all you have to do is make you client /server folder into a “.zip” file then make a new empty folder named exactly “META-INF” and then open the folder and open notepad then add the following lines exact in the quotes w/o the quotes
but in the * put the main class that it would open.

"

Manifest-Version: 1.0
Created-By: Signtool (signtool 1.3)

Name: *.class

"

I/e if you have to open client.class made by me it would be
"

Manifest-Version: 1.0
Created-By: JKOK

Name: client.class

"
but if its in another file it would be somthing like
(make sure the names dont have spaces instead have “_” I/e “my_client.class”
(make sure you don’t multi “.” your file name I/e “myclient.exe.class”

"

Manifest-Version: 1.0
Created-By: JKOK

Name: myserver.main.client.class

"

then save it into exact name " manifest.mf "

then copy that whole folder into the client’s or servers folder

then make sure the file is something like this picture (my newest java program ftw)
V
V
V

name it to what you want to name it to

then rename the file type to “.jar”

if you cannot see the file type search for google.com for the solution for you many types of computers

then if the source code works (if the original run works) double click it and it will open

feel free to uninstall jarmaker as most versions contain virus’s found by “iobit security 360”
(sorry to advertise it but it finds virus’s that most idiots put in their clients for "runserver,javafix,generators,autorun,jarmaker,etc (there some that dont have virus’s that are safe like lin’s interface maker, tom’s cache suite, etc)

(off topic)

if you see a server with a “.jar” extension file type or .exe run dont double click or run it

if it is “.jar” change the type to “.zip” and decompile the source code and look in it 1st[/quote]
Listen to this, IS IT YOUR TUTORIAL OR HIS?

soooo GTFO
